quoteFirst: Three days ago she confessed, received the sacrament and extreme unction; but since that time she has been constantly delirious and rambling, until this afternoon at twenty-one minutes after five, when she was seized with convulsions, and immediately lost all perception and feeling. I pressed her hand and spoke to her; but she neither saw me, heard me, nor seemed in the least sensible; and in this state she lay for five hours, namely, till
quoteLast: , when she departed, no one being present but myself, M. Haine, a good friend of ours whom my father knows, and the nurse.
title: Blackwood's Edinburgh Magazine, Volume 62, Number 361, November, 1845.
author: Various
